ass=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cim1665702692644.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cim1665702692644.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cim1665702692644.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cim1665702692644\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"cim1665702692644__uopract_406636\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Activate a component operation.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"cim1665702692644__topic_d122618e1_d122619e1_d122620e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104cim1665702692644_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"cim1665702692644__codeblock_lsh_zf2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">int uopract (UHACT hOpr, long* pStatus, long* pProcErr);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cim1665702692644__topic_d86792e1_d86793e1_d86794e1_d86795e1_d86796e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d678370e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"cim1665702692644__parml_x3m_1g2_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hOpr</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cim1665702692644__p_d122627e1_d122628e1_d122629e1\">The handle to the operation to be\n                     activated, as returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstopr</code>\n</p>\n</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">pStatus</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The activation status (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$status</code>).<p class=\"p\" id=\"cim1665702692644__p_d122633e1_d122634e1_d122635e1\">If you are not interested in this output,\n                     supply a zero value instead of a pointer.</p></dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">pProcErr</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The activation error status (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$procerror</code>).<p class=\"p\" id=\"cim1665702692644__p_d122639e1_d122640e1_d122641e1\">If you are not interested in this output,\n                     supply a zero value instead of a pointer.</p></dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cim1665702692644__topic_d86797e1_d86798e1_d86799e1_d86800e1_d86801e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d678370e116\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cim1665702692644__d5955e20\">For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return\n        Codes\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cim1665702692644__topic_d86802e1_d86803e1_d86804e1_d86805e1_d86806e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d678370e125\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cim1665702692644__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cim1665702692644__topic_d86807e1_d86808e1_d86809e1_d86810e1_d86811e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d678370e137\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cim1665702692644__p_d122657e1_d122658e1_d122659e1\">With this function, you can activate an operation\n            in an instantiated component, after you have obtained a handle to the operation by a\n            call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstopr</code> and (optionally) provided parameters. The function\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uopract</code> is the 3GL equivalent of the 4GL <code class=\"ph codeph\">activate</code>\n            ProcScript statement, and can return the same error codes.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cim1665702692644__p_d122660e1_d122661e1_d122662e1\">Note that, although the <var class=\"keyword varname\">pStatus</var>\n            and <var class=\"keyword varname\">pProcErr</var> variables are optional, it is good programming practice\n            to supply them, and to examine the status codes after return from\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uopract</code>. If you do not use these parameters, you have no way of\n            knowing whether your operation was successfully activated or what its return status\n            was.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cim1665702692644__section_kzs_fg2_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d678370e167\">Example: uecreate, uedelete, ufreeh, uinstdel, uinstnew, uinstopr, and\n            uopract</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following simple call-in program shows how to activate the EXEC\n            operation of the service MYSVC. As usual, error checking has been omitted for the sake\n            of brevity.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104cim1665702692644_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"cim1665702692644__codeblock_hzw_hg2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n\nvoid main (void)\n{\nUHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */\nUHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */\nUHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */\nlong opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */\n\n/* Create the environment */\nuecreate(1, 0, 0, \"my.asn\", 0, 0, &amp;hEnv);\n/* Instantiate service MYSVC */\nuinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &amp;hIn, 0);\n\nuinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &amp;hOp); /* Instantiate the EXEC operation */\nuopract (hOp, &amp;opStat, 0); /* Activate the operation */\nuinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */\n\nufreeh (&amp;hOp); /* Free the operation */\nufreeh (&amp;hIn); /* Free the instance */\nuedelete(hEnv, -1); /* Shut down the environment */\nufreeh (&amp;hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */\nreturn 0; // on success\t\t\t\t\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jhh1665702691902.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-In API Return Codes</a><p>Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pav1665702692575.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uinstopr</a><p>Return the handle to an operation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxx1665702529732.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>activate</a><p>Calls an operation on a component instance.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526462\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526462\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uopract Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Activate a component operation. Explain this code int uopract (UHACT hOpr, long* pStatus, long* pProcErr); Copy Parameters hOpr The handle to the operation to be activated, as returned by uinstopr pStatus (Output) The activation status ( $status ). If you are not interested in this output, supply a zero value instead of a pointer. pProcErr (Output) The activation error status ( $procerror ). If you are not interested in this output, supply a zero value instead of a pointer. Return Values For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return Codes\" topic. Use Library: ucall Description With this function, you can activate an operation in an instantiated component, after you have obtained a handle to the operation by a call to uinstopr and (optionally) provided parameters. The function uopract is the 3GL equivalent of the 4GL activate ProcScript statement, and can return the same error codes. Note that, although the pStatus and pProcErr variables are optional, it is good programming practice to supply them, and to examine the status codes after return from uopract . If you do not use these parameters, you have no way of knowing whether your operation was successfully activated or what its return status was. Example: uecreate, uedelete, ufreeh, uinstdel, uinstnew, uinstopr, and uopract The following simple call-in program shows how to activate the EXEC operation of the service MYSVC. As usual, error checking has been omitted for the sake of brevity. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> void main (void) { UHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */ UHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */ UHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */ long opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */ /* Create the environment */ uecreate(1, 0, 0, \"my.asn\", 0, 0, &hEnv); /* Instantiate service MYSVC */ uinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &hIn, 0); uinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &hOp); /* Instantiate the EXEC operation */ uopract (hOp, &opStat, 0); /* Activate the operation */ uinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */ ufreeh (&hOp); /* Free the operation */ ufreeh (&hIn); /* Free the instance */ uedelete(hEnv, -1); /* Shut down the environment */ ufreeh (&hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */ return 0; // on success } Copy Related Links Call-In API Return Codes Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise. uinstopr Return the handle to an operation. activate Calls an operation on a component instance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}